comments: Ayton (POR) maintains a hand against Gill's (WAS) body as he attempts the put-back.
Poole (WAS) legally contests Murray's (POR) driving shot attempt.
Henderson (POR) contests Poole's (WAS) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Omoruyi (WAS) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Ayton (POR) is still moving when contact occurs with Poole (WAS), but the contact is marginal during the defensive switch.
Banton (POR) places his hand against Gill's (WAS) hip and marginal contact occurs as Banton releases away to gather into his jump shot attempt.
Gill (WAS) contests Banton's (POR) jump shot and the contact after the release, and Baton's lower body, is marginal.
Omoruyi (WAS) initiates some contact with Murray's (POR) non-shooting arm during the last-second shot attempt, but the contact is marginal.
Murray's (POR) shot attempt does not contact the rim and the shot clock expires.
Gill (WAS) establishes himself in Henderson's (POR) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Gill (WAS) reaches for the rebound and marginal arm contact occurs with Walker (POR).

Walker (POR) and Omoruyi (WAS) inadvertently make head contact with each other as they come together.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Omoruyi's (WAS) left foot is out of bounds when he makes contact with the ball.
Avdija (WAS) extends his forearm into Henderson's (POR) head, initiating illegal contact during his driving shot attempt.
Henderson (POR) briefly engages and disengages with Poole (WAS) as the screen is set.
Walker (POR) grasps and quickly releases Kispert's (WAS) jersey as the screen is set.
Gill (WAS) establishes himself in Henderson's (POR) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Gill (WAS) and Henderson (POR) mutually engage and immediately disengage during the rebound.
